    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (74.75) and **Junior Caminero** (72.66) anchoring our offensive core. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a steady matchup against Warren, while **Junior Caminero** continues to profile as a must-start despite the park factor penalty; his 11% skill-based boost against the starter\u2019s xERA makes him an elite play in the #2 hole. Notably, **Caleb Durbin** presents the most intriguing value today with a 69.42 efficiency rating. While his batting order is suboptimal, the combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park and a high-leverage skill matchup against Young provides a massive 32% combined boost to his base projection, making him a high-upside play for stolen bases.\n\nWe are navigating a few situational constraints, primarily regarding our bench depth. **Carson Benge** was the clear runner-up for our final utility spot, scoring 48.62, but he was ultimately benched in favor of the higher-floor profiles of **Pete Crow-Armstrong** and **Josh Smith**. While **Pete Crow-Armstrong** faces a difficult matchup against Sheehan\u2014resulting in a sharp 19% downgrade due to the pitcher\u2019s elite metrics\u2014his dynamic platoon advantage and defensive upside keep him in the fold. Conversely, **Josh Smith** remains a volatile asset; while his 59.04 score is bolstered by a strong platoon edge, the defensive prowess of the opposing catcher threatens his stolen base ceiling. As we look at the remainder of our bench, **Christian Yelich** remains sidelined, and both **Colt Keith** and **Victor Scott II** are out of the starting lineup today, further limiting our ability to pivot if these projections shift as official lineups finalize.",
